    "content_blocks_QnK8qK": {
      "type": "content-blocks",
      "blocks": {
        "content_block_eqwc7Y": {
          "type": "content-block",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "logo",
            "heading": "Explosion Proof Capable Power Connectors & Cable Assemblies",
            "content": "<p>Global Intex designs and manufactures heavy-duty power connectors and ruggedized cable assemblies with Ex Proofing options built for environments where abrasion, vibration, and ignition risk are a constant operational reality. Carrying country-specific Ex approvals including IECEx, ATEX, and FM certifications, our connectors are engineered with exotic materials and customized overmolding to deliver reliable power connectivity in underground mining, onshore and offshore gas and oil, and other hazardous location applications.</p>",
            "link_text": "Link text",
            "link_url": ""
          }
        },
        "content_block_Vmn9Re": {
          "type": "content-block",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "logo",
            "heading": "Wire Harness Systems for Extreme Industrial Applications",
            "content": "<p>From complex multi-conductor harness builds to proprietary OEM configurations, Global Intex engineers and manufactures wire harness systems designed to survive vibration, abrasion, chemical exposure, and extreme temperatures in the field. Built around specialized rubber extrusion and customized overmolding processes, these harness systems are purpose-built for deployment in mining equipment, agricultural machinery, marine systems, and heavy industrial platforms.</p>",
            "link_text": "Link text",
            "link_url": ""
          }
        },
        "content_block_ccRynD": {
          "type": "content-block",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "logo",
            "heading": "Wet-Mate & Dry-Mate Submersible Cabling, Power, and Data Transfer Connectors",
            "content": "<p>Global Intex offers both wet-mate and dry-mate submersible cabling solutions engineered for reliable power and signal transmission in shallow and deep-water applications across fresh water and salt water environments. Wet-mate configurations allow safe connection and disconnection while submerged, making them ideal for ROV systems, underwater instrumentation, and subsea infrastructure. Our dry-mate submersible cabling is designed for connections made above the waterline and then deployed, offering robust sealing and long-term performance across a wide range of underwater operating depths and conditions.</p>",
            "link_text": "Link text",
            "link_url": ""
          }
        },
        "content_block_9iwXiw": {
          "type": "content-block",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "logo",
            "heading": "Custom & Proprietary Builds for OEMs and Contract Manufacturers",
            "content": "<p>Global Intex welcomes complex, custom connectivity challenges. With a specialized engineering staff and comprehensive in-house manufacturing center based in Mentor, Ohio, our team works directly with OEMs and contract manufacturers to develop proprietary connector and harness builds that meet precise performance, certification, and form-factor requirements. From material selection and tooling through production and quality verification, Global Intex functions as a true manufacturing partner with additional catalog offerings.</p>",
            "link_text": "Link text",
            "link_url": ""
          }
        }
      },
